makediary (0.2.1-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Allow starting the diary on an arbitrary day with --start-date.
  * Allow an arbitrary title on the cover page.

 -- Russell Steicke <russells@adelie.cx>  Mon, 20 Mar 2005 15:40:47 +0800

makediary (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added vi, vim and unix reference pages.  Vi and vim pages are (C) Donald
    Bindner, available under GFDL.  Unix page was based on those.
  * Can stop smiley printing on cover page, if you wish.
  * Added option to print a day per page.  In this mode you get a year's worth
    of month calendars across the bottom of each opening.
  * Expanded the man page.
  * Moved to gnuarch for revision control.

 -- Russell Steicke <russells@adelie.cx>  Thu, 07 Oct 2004 10:12:00 +1100

